# Pull requests

Full guides: `docs/contributing/pull-requests.md`, `docs/contributing/branches.md`

## PR title

Conventional Commits format, English: `feat(scope): short description`

## PR body template

```markdown
## Summary
- <1-3 bullet points>

## Test plan
- [ ] <verification step>
```

## Before opening a PR

- Branch up to date with base branch
- All CI checks pass locally (lint, unit, integration, build)
- No secrets or generated artifacts that should be gitignored
- Tests included for new/changed behavior (TDD)
- ADR linked if architecture decision was made

## Review focus

- Security (OWASP, auth, input validation)
- Query count per route (N+1)
- Complexity and file size limits
- Tenant isolation (if applicable)
- English-only code and comments
